    "headline": "Marvell Stock Was Just Added to S&P 500. Here’s Who Else Was Included and Bumped.",
    "summary": "Marvell Technology  and  Flex  will be added to the  index, replacing  Pool  and  Campbell’s  the soup company, prior to the opening of trading on June 22, according to S&P Dow Jones Indices.  Before its deletion, Campbell’s had one of the smallest market values in the S&P 500, making it vulnerable to deletion.  Marvell was famously tagged as the next $1 trillion company by  Nvidia  CEO Jensen Huang earlier this week.",
